column3: Couldn't you have merged this into one of the two just-merged typo PRs. Rather than opening an pull-request to fix the same thing.\n\nI can't believe new typos are being re-introduced this quickly anyways.

These typos were are all introduced in fairly recently merged PRs:

* `src/init.cpp`: minimimum (minimum) - typo introduced in 7b1add3c28aae8caf2e1517f15cd953eacbb4931 on December 13:th
* `src/rpc/client.cpp`: Specifiy (Specify) - typo introduced in 481f289765fab47ff2e0bd7dfb968f2bd92fd608 on November 12:th
* `src/rpc/misc.cpp`: callsites (call sites) - typo introduced in 99464bc38e9575ff4
utACK 2152f8e. In the future I'd suggest this is done only every 6 months (prior to every release).

utACK 0c9b9b7.\n\n@practicalswift If you find some more typos, that is great, but please wait a few months until submitting a pull request. We have no pressure to fix all typos immediately, it is enough to do it twice a year or something.
